[This BBC report is 16 months old but it provides some background,
even if dated. I went through my 1988-2008 notes for anthrax in the
Balkan countries. For what it is worth: Albania: enzootic in
livestock; 2007, 82 human cases; 2008, 33 human cases. From our
genomic studies it is largely an A1.a country. Bosnia: sporadic
Bulgaria: sporadic but low numbers of human cases each year. Greece:
enzootic but recently livestock outbreak numbers are reduced;
routinely seen in humans. Kosovo: sporadic. Macedonia: sporadic with
human cases each year. Montenegro: sporadic. Serbia: sporadic with
human cases. - Mod.MHJ]

