[2]
Date: Sun 11 Jan 2010 [accessed Wed 3 Feb 2010]
Source: The Telegraph [edited]
<http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/6967549/Men-jailed-over-biggest-heroin-seizure.html>


Men jailed over biggest heroin seizure
--------------------------------------
Three men were jailed today [11 Jan 2010] for their parts in a GBP 33
million drugs deal that led to the biggest heroin seizure made by
British police, Scotland Yard said. [The 3 men, aged, 32, 35, and 30],
were convicted of conspiracy to supply heroin after officers seized
nearly 730 lb (330 kg) of the substance at a motorway service station
in 2008.

Kingston Crown Court sentenced [the 32-year-old], of Upton Lane, near
Stratford, east London, to 17 years, [the 35-year-old], of Brixham
Gardens, Ilford, east London, to 15 and a half years, and [the
30-year-old], of Cavendish Gardens, Ilford, to 23 years. His trial
heard that a 37-year-old Dutchman drove a BMW estate through Customs
at Dover in Kent on the afternoon of 8 Apr 2008.

A few hours later police stopped [the Dutchman] at a service station
near Maidstone and found 11 large boxes of heroin in his car. [The
32-year-old convicted man] had arrived at the services shortly
beforehand, and police discovered that a further 2 boxes of the drug
had been transferred to his Seat Leon. Together the 13 boxes contained
729 lb (330.7 kg) of heroin, with a street value of more than GBP 33
million, the court was told.

[The 35-year-old man] pleaded guilty to conspiracy to supply heroin in
September 2008, [the 32-year-old] was found guilty of the same offence
last June [2009], and [the 30-year-old] was convicted in December
[2009]. [The Dutchman] was found guilty of importing the heroin and
jailed for 26 years at an earlier hearing.

Detective inspector Marion Ryan, from the Met's central task force,
said: "This is the biggest heroin seizure we know of by any UK police
force. Today's [11 Jan 2010] result is testimony to how the Met has
prevented the serious consequences this conspiracy could have had on
people's lives."

