[This recent conviction report would indicate that the facts in the
2008 BBC report are still relevant. - Mod.MHJ]

[The figures boggle the mind. There are an estimated 280 000 problem
drug users in the UK, most taking heroin and crack cocaine (and around
2500 deaths a year). 140 000 heroin users needing 1 gram for 10-50
hits, averaging 3 hits a day, depending on level of addiction, would
consume 140 kg, so 330 kg wouldn't go that far. Much more than this
must be being smuggled in every year. - Mod.JW]
